#: ../../A/AFAIK.rst:5
msgid "AFAIK"
msgstr "AFAIK"

#: ../../A/AFAIK.rst:7
msgid "//, n\\."
msgstr "//, 名詞"

#: ../../A/AFAIK.rst:9
msgid ""
"[Usenet; common] Abbrev. for \"As Far As I Know\". There is a variant AFAICT"
" \"As Far As I Can Tell\"; where AFAIK suggests that the writer knows his "
"knowledge is limited, AFAICT suggests that he feels his knowledge is as "
"complete as anybody else's but that the best available knowledge does not "
"support firm conclusions."
msgstr ""
"[Usenet。一般的]「As Far As I Know(私の知る限り)」の略。AFAICT「As Far As I Can "
"Tell(私が判断できる限り)」という異形がある。AFAIKが、書き手は自分の知識が限られていると認識していることを示唆するのに対し、AFAICTは、自分の知識は他の誰にも劣らず完全だと感じてはいるが、得られる最良の知識をもってしても確たる結論は出せない、ということを示唆する。"
